## 6. Advanced Mitigation Techniques

### 6.1 UX Signals That Increase Trust Score

TikTok's content analysis evaluates whether a linked page is a **real page** or a **redirect/funnel page**. Maximize "real page" signals:

| Signal | Implementation |
|---|---|
| **Genuine content** | The link-in-bio page should have a real bio, description, and brand identity — not just a list of links. |
| **Multiple diverse links** | Include 4–6 links (not just Telegram + website). Add Instagram, Twitter/X, YouTube, email, etc. This signals a legitimate multi-platform presence, not a single-destination funnel. |
| **Contact information** | A `mailto:` link or contact form path signals legitimacy. |
| **Consistent branding** | Logo, colors, typography matching your main website. Crawlers compare visual consistency across domains. |
| **Accessibility** | Proper semantic HTML, ARIA labels, alt text. Legitimate businesses invest in accessibility. Scrapers and throwaway funnel pages never do. |
| **Legal pages** | Link to privacy policy and terms of service (can be on your main domain). |

### 6.2 Domain & Subdomain Strategy

```
yourbrand.com           ← Main website (primary domain, aged, trusted)
├── links.yourbrand.com ← Link-in-bio (inherits parent trust)
├── www.yourbrand.com   ← Main website (canonical)
└── api.yourbrand.com   ← API (if needed)
```

**Critical rules:**

- **Do NOT use a separate domain** for the link-in-bio page if you can avoid it. A subdomain of your main domain inherits trust.
- **Register your domain early.** If your domain is <30 days old when TikTok first scans it, expect heightened scrutiny. Ideally, let the domain age for 3+ months with real content before using it in a TikTok bio.
- **Use a reputable registrar** (Cloudflare, Namecheap, Google Domains). Avoid registrars popular with spammers.
- **Use a reputable host** (Vercel, Cloudflare Pages, Netlify). Shared hosting on an IP with bad neighbors hurts you.

### 6.3 Reducing False-Positive Signals

| Technique | Details |
|---|---|
| **Avoid URL shorteners in the chain** | No `bit.ly`, `tinyurl`, etc. These are high-risk signals. Links should be readable. |
| **Avoid parameter-heavy URLs** | `links.yourbrand.com` > `links.yourbrand.com/?ref=tiktok&campaign=q1&utm_source=...`. Keep the bio URL clean. Track via other means. |
| **Serve identical content to all clients** | Never vary content based on user-agent, IP, or referrer. Cloaking detection is a **ban-level** offense. The TikTok crawler should see exactly what users see. |
| **Keep the page fast** | Slow-loading pages that eventually redirect are flagged. Your link-in-bio page should achieve <2s LCP (Largest Contentful Paint). |
| **Use HTTPS everywhere** | This should be obvious but: no mixed content, no HTTP fallbacks, valid certificate. |
| **Don't rotate destinations** | If different users clicking the same link land on different pages, that's a cloaking signal. One URL = one destination, always. |

### 6.4 Analytics Tracking Approach

**The wrong way** (suspicious):
- Third-party tracking pixels from unknown domains
- Multiple analytics scripts loading external resources
- URL parameters that change per-click (`?clickid=abc123`)
- Server-side redirect that logs clicks and forwards (adds a hop)

**The right way** (invisible to detection):

```javascript
// /api/track.js — First-party API endpoint on the SAME domain
export default function handler(req, res) {
  if (req.method !== 'POST') return res.status(405).end();
  
  const { event, linkId, timestamp, referrer } = JSON.parse(req.body);
  
  // Store in your database (MongoDB, Postgres, etc.)
  // This is a same-origin POST — no cross-domain requests,
  // no tracking pixels, no external scripts.
  await db.collection('analytics').insertOne({
    event,
    linkId,
    timestamp,
    referrer,
    userAgent: req.headers['user-agent'],
    ip: req.headers['x-forwarded-for']?.split(',')[0],  // For geo
    createdAt: new Date(),
  });

  res.status(204).end();
}
```

**Key principles:**
- **First-party only.** All tracking requests go to your own domain (`links.yourbrand.com/api/track`). No third-party scripts.
- **Use `navigator.sendBeacon()`** for click tracking. It's non-blocking and doesn't delay navigation.
- **No tracking in the URL.** The URL in TikTok's bio is clean: `links.yourbrand.com`. Referrer headers tell you the traffic source.
- **Server-side analytics for the redirect page.** When `/go/website` is loaded, log the visit server-side in `getServerSideProps` before rendering the page. This captures visits even if JS is disabled (i.e., crawlers).

### 6.5 Telegram Link Mitigation

Since Telegram links carry inherent risk, reduce their signal weight:

1. **Don't put Telegram first** in your link list. Lead with your website, then social platforms, then Telegram. Order signals priority.
2. **Use descriptive labels.** "Join Our Community" is better than "Telegram" in the link text (though the `href` will still be `t.me/*`).
3. **Consider a Telegram redirect page** (`/go/community`) that explains what the community is about before linking out. This adds value and context.
4. **Have at least 3 other links** on the page. A page with just "Website" and "Telegram" looks like a funnel. A page with 5–6 links looks like a genuine link hub.

